  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nPlease note that this is an issue tracker reserved for bug reports and feature requests.\r\n\r\nFor general questions please use the gitter channel or the Ethereum stack exchange at https://ethereum.stackexchange.com.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.9.6\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nNoPruning = true in the dumped config\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nNoPruning = false in the dumped config\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nWe have a geth.toml that includes:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[Eth]\r\nNetworkId = 1\r\nSyncMode = \"full\"\r\nDatabaseCache = 4096\r\nNoPruning = true\r\n```\r\n\r\nI would expect this to enable an archival gc mode (we've been running with --gcmode=archiva as a cli flag until now). To verify this, I tried to read the config in and then dump it using:\r\n\r\n    geth --config=/var/lib/blockchains/ethereum/geth.toml dumpconfig\r\n\r\nHowever, this gives me a config dump with `NoPruning = false`",
